We estimated life expectancy at birth for Gaucher disease type 1 (GD1) patients 
by comparing survival data from GD1 patients enrolled in ICGG Gaucher Registry 
to the U.S. population using standard life table methods. 2,876 GD1 patients had 
102 reported deaths in 13,509 person-years of follow-up. Estimated life 
expectancy at birth was 68 y, compared with 77 y in reference population; 
splenectomized patients, 64 y; nonsplenectomized, 72 y. Causes of death for 
63/102 patients were malignancy (17/63), cardiovascular (11/63), and 
cerebrovascular (8/63). Estimated life expectancy at birth for GD1 patients was 
approximately 9 y less than reference population. Malignancies did not 
contribute to shortened life expectancy.

